    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.accounts.create(name: string, type: string, account_number?: string, account_role?: 'defaultAsset' | 'sharedAsset' | 'savingAsset' | 'ccAsset' | 'cashWalletAsset', active?: boolean, bic?: string, credit_card_type?: 'monthlyFull', currency_code?: string, currency_id?: string, iban?: string, include_net_worth?: boolean, interest?: string, interest_period?: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly' | 'quarterly' | 'half-year' | 'yearly', latitude?: number, liability_direction?: 'credit' | 'debit', liability_type?: 'loan' | 'debt' | 'mortgage', longitude?: number, monthly_payment_date?: string, notes?: string, opening_balance?: string, opening_balance_date?: string, order?: number, virtual_balance?: string, zoom_level?: number, X-Trace-Id?: string): { data: account_read; }`\n\n**post** `/v1/accounts`\n\nCreates a new account. The data required can be submitted as a JSON body or as a list of parameters (in key=value pairs, like a webform).\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `name: string`\n\n- `type: string`\n  Can only be one one these account types. import, initial-balance and reconciliation cannot be set manually.\n\n- `account_number?: string`\n\n- `account_role?: 'defaultAsset' | 'sharedAsset' | 'savingAsset' | 'ccAsset' | 'cashWalletAsset'`\n  Is only mandatory when the type is asset.\n\n- `active?: boolean`\n  If omitted, defaults to true.\n\n- `bic?: string`\n\n- `credit_card_type?: 'monthlyFull'`\n  Mandatory when the account_role is ccAsset. Can only be monthlyFull or null.\n\n- `currency_code?: string`\n  Use either currency_id or currency_code. Defaults to the user's financial administration's currency.\n\n- `currency_id?: string`\n  Use either currency_id or currency_code. Defaults to the user's financial administration's currency.\n\n- `iban?: string`\n\n- `include_net_worth?: boolean`\n  If omitted, defaults to true.\n\n- `interest?: string`\n  Mandatory when type is liability. Interest percentage.\n\n- `interest_period?: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly' | 'quarterly' | 'half-year' | 'yearly'`\n  Mandatory when type is liability. Period over which the interest is calculated.\n\n- `latitude?: number`\n  Latitude of the accounts's location, if applicable. Can be used to draw a map.\n\n- `liability_direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'`\n  'credit' indicates somebody owes you the liability. 'debit' Indicates you owe this debt yourself. Works only for liabilities.\n\n- `liability_type?: 'loan' | 'debt' | 'mortgage'`\n  Mandatory when type is liability. Specifies the exact type.\n\n- `longitude?: number`\n  Latitude of the accounts's location, if applicable. Can be used to draw a map.\n\n- `monthly_payment_date?: string`\n  Mandatory when the account_role is ccAsset. Moment at which CC payment installments are asked for by the bank.\n\n- `notes?: string`\n\n- `opening_balance?: string`\n  Represents the opening balance, the initial amount this account holds.\n\n- `opening_balance_date?: string`\n  Represents the date of the opening balance.\n\n- `order?: number`\n  Order of the account\n\n- `virtual_balance?: string`\n\n- `zoom_level?: number`\n  Zoom level for the map, if drawn. This to set the box right. Unfortunately this is a proprietary value because each map provider has different zoom levels.\n\n- `X-Trace-Id?: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data: { id: string; attributes: object; type: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data: { id: string; attributes: { name: string; type: string; account_number?: string; account_role?: 'defaultAsset' | 'sharedAsset' | 'savingAsset' | 'ccAsset' | 'cashWalletAsset'; active?: boolean; balance_difference?: string; bic?: string; created_at?: string; credit_card_type?: 'monthlyFull'; currency_code?: string; currency_decimal_places?: number; currency_id?: string; currency_name?: string; currency_symbol?: string; current_balance?: string; current_balance_date?: string; debt_amount?: string; iban?: string; include_net_worth?: boolean; interest?: string; interest_period?: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly' | 'quarterly' | 'half-year' | 'yearly'; last_activity?: string; latitude?: number; liability_direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'; liability_type?: 'loan' | 'debt' | 'mortgage'; longitude?: number; monthly_payment_date?: string; notes?: string; object_group_id?: string; object_group_order?: number; object_group_title?: string; object_has_currency_setting?: boolean; opening_balance?: string; opening_balance_date?: string; order?: number; pc_balance_difference?: string; pc_current_balance?: string; pc_debt_amount?: string; pc_opening_balance?: string; pc_virtual_balance?: string; primary_currency_code?: string; primary_currency_decimal_places?: number; primary_currency_id?: string; primary_currency_name?: string; primary_currency_symbol?: string; updated_at?: string; virtual_balance?: string; zoom_level?: number; }; type: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Firefly from 'firefly-iii-api';\n\nconst client = new Firefly();\n\nconst accountSingle = await client.accounts.create({ name: 'My checking account', type: 'asset' });\n\nconsole.log(accountSingle);\n```",
