    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.rules.create(actions: { type: string; value: string; active?: boolean; order?: number; stop_processing?: boolean; }[], rule_group_id: string, title: string, trigger: 'store-journal' | 'update-journal' | 'manual-activation', triggers: { type: string; value: string; active?: boolean; order?: number; prohibited?: boolean; stop_processing?: boolean; }[], active?: boolean, description?: string, order?: number, rule_group_title?: string, stop_processing?: boolean, strict?: boolean, X-Trace-Id?: string): { data: rule_read; }`\n\n**post** `/v1/rules`\n\nCreates a new rule. The data required can be submitted as a JSON body or as a list of parameters.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `actions: { type: string; value: string; active?: boolean; order?: number; stop_processing?: boolean; }[]`\n\n- `rule_group_id: string`\n  ID of the rule group under which the rule must be stored. Either this field or rule_group_title is mandatory.\n\n- `title: string`\n\n- `trigger: 'store-journal' | 'update-journal' | 'manual-activation'`\n  Which action is necessary for the rule to fire? Use either store-journal, update-journal or manual-activation.\n\n- `triggers: { type: string; value: string; active?: boolean; order?: number; prohibited?: boolean; stop_processing?: boolean; }[]`\n\n- `active?: boolean`\n  Whether or not the rule is even active. Default is true.\n\n- `description?: string`\n\n- `order?: number`\n\n- `rule_group_title?: string`\n  Title of the rule group under which the rule must be stored. Either this field or rule_group_id is mandatory.\n\n- `stop_processing?: boolean`\n  If this value is true and the rule is triggered, other rules  after this one in the group will be skipped. Default value is false.\n\n- `strict?: boolean`\n  If the rule is set to be strict, ALL triggers must hit in order for the rule to fire. Otherwise, just one is enough. Default value is true.\n\n- `X-Trace-Id?: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data: { id: string; attributes: object; links: object_link; type: string; }; }`\n\n  - `data: { id: string; attributes: { actions: { type: rule_action_keyword; value: string; id?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; order?: number; stop_processing?: boolean; updated_at?: string; }[]; rule_group_id: string; title: string; trigger: 'store-journal' | 'update-journal' | 'manual-activation'; triggers: { type: rule_trigger_keyword; value: string; id?: string; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; order?: number; prohibited?: boolean; stop_processing?: boolean; updated_at?: string; }[]; active?: boolean; created_at?: string; description?: string; order?: number; rule_group_title?: string; stop_processing?: boolean; strict?: boolean; updated_at?: string; }; links: { 0?: object; self?: string; }; type: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Firefly from 'firefly-iii-api';\n\nconst client = new Firefly();\n\nconst ruleSingle = await client.rules.create({\n  actions: [{ type: 'set_category', value: 'Daily groceries' }],\n  rule_group_id: '81',\n  title: 'First rule title.',\n  trigger: 'store-journal',\n  triggers: [{ type: 'from_account_starts', value: 'tag1' }],\n});\n\nconsole.log(ruleSingle);\n```",
